history.content:
120 doesn't need any Simulink and is mostly problem sets by hand. Some problems are done in Matlab (this semester we're doing them in python), but should be simple enough that coding isn't a requirement (more like FFT this and that). EE120 is a medium-light workload and is more of a math class too.

----------

Courtade will teach in Spring if I am correct. He tends to be a very nice professor and he uses Matlab, at least used Matlab when I took this class with him. Light side in terms of the workload, one problem set every two weeks usually and two midterms.
